<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. SEEKS SYRIA'S HELP IN MIDEAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is in response to the letter (Sept. 9) by Richard Boyce, stating that 
Israel has "unmitigated gall" in asking for its debt also to be forgiven. 
</P>
<P>
Was it unmitigated gall to bomb the nuclear reactor in Iraq and thus save the 
world from a holocaust in 1990? Who but Israel saved Jordan from invasion by 
Syria or Iraq, warning them that such a step would meet with the Israel Defense 
Force? 
</P>
<P>
Israel's stabilizing influence in the region is priceless. 
</P>
<P>
BERNARD LEVINE 
</P>
<P>
La Jolla 
</P>
