<P>
BOOK COLLECTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a lifelong bibliophile, I'm delighted to see that news about books is making 
the front page ("The Binding Attraction of Books" by Terry Pristin, Aug. 30). 
</P>
<P>
It is impressive to read all about the prominent people who have taken up book 
collecting as a hobby but there is one element about books that seems to be 
overlooked: It's fun. You don't have to be rich and famous to enjoy books. And 
now that it has become a status symbol to be surrounded by books, I've been 
appalled to see expensive homes decorated with wallpaper with books sketched 
in, instead of real shelves overflowing with books. That's where the fun is! 
</P>
