<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAN'T UNDERSTAND USC FOOTBALL PRIORITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In August, the Times reported that three USC freshman football players have 
been accused of sexually assaulting a female grad student, and that Coach Larry 
Smith had suspended the three players. 
</P>
<P>
Yet, in the Sept. 11 Times I read that one of the three players was in the 
starting lineup in the season opener against Syracuse, replacing a player who 
was late for a team meal. 
</P>
<P>
I am a die-hard Trojan fan, but I can't support a team that would promote a 
player who is accused of sexually assaulting a woman because they want to 
punish a player who was late for a team meal. Strange priorities at USC. 
</P>
<P>
CHRIS CLARK 
</P>
<P>
San Marino 
</P>
<P>
 Editor's note: The Times reported that the three players were put on 
probation, not suspended, pending completion of an investigation by the Los 
Angeles City Attorney's office. That investigation is continuing. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
