<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. OPEN SERVES TENNIS WITH POTENTIAL PROBLEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Open tennis tournament was entertaining at its best, but the 
magnificent performance of Pete Sampras has served to place a dark cloud on the 
horizon for this and other tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
His awesome serve was so dominant that it could be the forerunner of a trend to 
place too high a dividend on that one facet to the detriment of finesse and 
many other exciting nuances of the game. 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps some thought should be given to raising the net a few inches or 
shortening the service area to prevent the power play from making a mockery of 
the game. 
</P>
<P>
BILL KRAUSE 
</P>
<P>
Palm Springs 
</P>
</TEXT>
