<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV GEOGRAPHY, UCLA FOOTBALL TEAM MATCH MARKS OF 'F' IN OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I thought football was complicated, but Terry Donahue says it's simple. 
</P>
<P>
I thought UCLA was clobbered by Oklahoma last Saturday because the Bruins were 
outplayed and out-coached. But Donahue informs us it was because of two dropped 
punts. 
</P>
<P>
His genius is being wasted. He should leave the coaching of Bruin football to 
lesser minds and figure out how to ship Medflies to Iraq and how to keep Bert 
Parks out of Atlantic City. 
</P>
<P>
MARSHALL L. HUTCHASON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
