<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV GEOGRAPHY, UCLA FOOTBALL TEAM MATCH MARKS OF 'F' IN OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About the only good thing that happened to the UCLA Bruins in their dismal loss 
to Oklahoma was the end of their quarterback controversy. 
</P>
<P>
Redshirt freshman Tommy Maddox obviously should be that starting quarterback 
for the next four years. 
</P>
<P>
Should the UCLA coaching brain trust grasp this fact, they will then be able to 
devote their attention to where it is most needed: teaching the offensive line 
to block. 
</P>
<P>
GEORGE GODLIN 
</P>
<P>
Corona 
</P>
