<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEAN TO MACLAINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have never liked the term mean-spirited, mostly because I did not quite 
understand it. 
</P>
<P>
However, thanks to Don Shirley's Aug. 30 review of Shirley MacLaine's "Out 
There Tonight," I do now. 
</P>
<P>
Most of his criticism is leveled at the fact that a great deal of the show is 
repetitive of previous shows. Since when is this a sin? Why not repeat proven 
material? 
</P>
<P>
Also, what about those of us who have not seen MacLaine previously? Are we to 
be discouraged because Don Shirley has? 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD GENOVESE 
</P>
<P>
Toluca Lake 
</P>
</TEXT>
