VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
INDEPENDENCE FIESTA TO FEATURE CELEBRITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAJA RADEVICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former Dallas Cowboys football player, Mexican entertainers and local singers 
and dancers will join today in Ventura County's Las Fiestas Patrias, an annual 
celebration of Mexico's independence from Spain. 
</P>
<P>
Singer Liz Navar will serve as grand marshal of the parade at 11 a.m. today on 
C Street in downtown Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
Efren Herrera, former place-kicker for the Dallas Cowboys, will appear. 
</P>
<P>
Opening ceremonies start at 7 a.m. in Plaza Park at 5th and C streets. Local 
performing groups are featured the rest of the morning. A ceremony with Mexican 
Consulate Zoila A. De Rodriguez will be held at 10:45 a.m. Entertainment groups 
from Chihuahua, Jalisco and Durango will be featured until 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday's performances, which will take place on two stages, start at 10 a.m. 
and will be broadcast live on Jones Intercable from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.; on KTRO 
Spanish Radio from 2 to 6 p.m.; and on KOXR Spanish Radio from 6 to 10 p.m. 
MAJA RADEVICH 
</P>
