DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VAN NUYS WOMAN, 41, DIES IN TRUCK COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 41-year old Van Nuys woman was killed when her car collided with a 
tractor-trailer truck in Sherman Oaks on Friday afternoon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Fariba Solhjoe died at UCLA Medical Center, said Officer Michael Brausam. The 
accident occurred shortly after 1 p.m. as Solhjoe was traveling north on 
Beverly Glen Boulevard, a quarter-mile north of Mulholland Drive. "She veered 
left over the double yellow lines" and "went underneath the tractor-trailer 
rig," Brausam said. 
</P>
<P>
The front of Solhjoe's 1980 Nissan Sentra was run over by the left rear wheels 
of the truck. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck was not injured. 
</P>
