<HEADLINE>
<P>
A PLEA FOR THE TREES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Excess tree trimming is going on in the West Valley, where they are cutting 
over 70% of healthy branches for no reason at all. I understand that if a tree 
presents a hazard, it should be taken care of, but this is not the case. 
</P>
<P>
When I called City Hall and spoke with the person in charge of the project, he 
told me that there is not much that he could do, because these so-called "tree 
trimmers" (I'll call them "tree killers") are private contractors and they have 
to cut as much as possible to make a profit. 
</P>
<P>
So, who is in charge? How can we stop them before they destroy the beauty of 
our trees and deprive us of shade on our sidewalks? 
</P>
<P>
The city should use the money to plant trees, not to kill them. 
</P>
<P>
CARLOS LACAMARA 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
