<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 13 ARRESTED AT PROTEST OVER EL SALVADOR 
POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thirteen people protesting U.S. policy in El Salvador were arrested after a 
mass protest that stopped traffic and created a blocks-long jam in West Los 
Angeles Friday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
The 3 p.m. protest, outside the office of U.S. Sen. Pete Wilson (R-Calif.) at 
Santa Monica and Sepulveda boulevards, drew more than 100 protesters who 
demanded that Wilson oppose aid to El Salvador, said an organizer, Neile 
Rissmiller. 
</P>
<P>
Eight men and five women were arrested and released on $250 bail, police said. 
The demonstration, organized by the Committee in Solidarity with the People of 
El Salvador, shut down the eastbound lanes of Santa Monica Boulevard and tied 
up traffic on nearby freeway ramps. 
</P>
</TEXT>
