<P>
The U.S. soccer team will play Trinidad and Tobago, the team the Americans 
defeated to qualify for the World Cup, today at High Point, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
The United States' 1-0 upset of Trinidad and Tobago in Port of Spain last 
spring sent the team to the World Cup for the first time in 40 years. 
</P>
<P>
For the rematch, the rosters of both teams are depleted because some of the top 
players have signed with European clubs. 
</P>
<P>
The match will mark the return of forward Peter Vermes, who injured his ankle 
at the World Cup in June and has not played since. 
</P>
<P>
Another addition to the U.S. roster is Anton Nistl of Los Angeles. Nistl was an 
All-American goalkeeper at UCLA and played for the San Diego Nomads of the APSL 
West. 
