<P>
RAIDERS; 
</P>
<P>
MOSEBAR NAMED CAPTAIN OF OFFENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Raiders selected center Don Mosebar as captain of the offensive unit, 
linebacker Jerry Robinson as defensive captain and center Dan Turk as special 
teams captain. 
</P>
<P>
Turk replaced Stefon Adams, last year's special teams captain, who was signed 
by the Cleveland Browns after being waived by the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
Wide receiver Willie Gault was a member of a three-man team that set a track 
record Tuesday in the National Bobsled Push Championship at Lake Placid, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Gault teamed with Olympic hurdler Edwin Moses and Bubba Womack to post a record 
time of 5.18 seconds on one run. They won the three-heat competition in 15.68 
seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Running back Herschel Walker of the Minnesota Vikings was originally on the 
team but dropped out because of an injury. 
</P>
<P>
Gault, a member of the 1988 U.S. Olympic bobsled team, said his goal is to win 
a Super Bowl ring and an Olympic gold medal. 
</P>
<P>
Defensive tackle Cortez Kennedy, the Seattle Seahawks' No. 1 draft choice, will 
probably beplaying more Sunday against the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
The third player picked in the NFL draft, Kennedy was on the field for only 20 
plays during last week's 17-0 loss to the Bears in Chicago, after missing the 
exhibition season because of a holdout. CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
