<HEADLINE>
<P>
6-YEAR-OLD BOY DROWNS IN SHALLOW END OF APARTMENT POOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 6-year-old boy drowned in the shallow end of a swimming pool at an apartment 
complex Friday despite efforts by other swimmers to revive him, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Miguel Martinez, who could not swim, was wading in the shallow end of a pool at 
2200 E. Santa Clara Ave., accompanied by his mother, at about 5:50 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
"Suddenly, they discovered he was missing. 
</P>
<P>
They found him lying in the shallow end of the pool," said Senior Deputy 
Coroner Richard McAnally. 
</P>
<P>
Attempts to revive the boy were unsuccessful, and paramedics took him to 
Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, where he was pronounced dead less than two 
hours later. 
</P>
<P>
The boy's parents were identified as Atapita and Jose Martinez of Santa Ana. 
The family was visiting relatives at the apartment complex, authorities said. 
</P>
