<TEXT>
<P>
Boycott Urged: Angered by a price increase announced last week, some users of 
the Prodigy electronic communication service asking other subscribers not to 
buy products promoted through advertisements on the service. A large-scale 
boycott could be a setback for Prodigy, a joint venture of Sears, Roebuck &amp; 
Co. and International Business Machines that has yet to turn a profit. The 
company's new pricing system raises monthly rates by $3-top $12.95-for those 
who pay on a monthly basis. 
