U.S. Wants to Forgive Some Debtors: President Bush sent Congress a bill to 
forgive $7 billion in Latin American debt and to encourage more U.S. companies 
to invest there. Bush reportedly would also like to have the authority to lower 
trade barriers with Mexico in hand when he meets with President Carlos Salinas 
de Gortari in November. 
