<TEXT>
<P>
Navy Exonerates IBM: The Navy said International Business Machines did not 
break federal contracting laws by providing advice and training for Navy 
personnel when it hoped to win lucrative mainframe contracts. Congress held 
hearings last November into allegations by smaller companies that IBM might be 
breaking laws in seeking military contracts. The Navy said a contracting 
official sought advice from IBM in drawing up specifications, but IBM did not 
initiate the offer. 
</P>
